<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="913" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d913">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111So4/71</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The French Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_JJAAJ1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jusserand</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 30, 1915</hi>
                                </date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received January 3,
                                1916</hi>.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: The information mentioned
                            in your letter of the 28th concerning Mr. <persName>Thaw</persName>, Mr.
                                <persName>Cowdin</persName> and Mr. <persName>Prince</persName> was
                            known to me, but, as you surmised, only from the papers. I cabled at
                            once to my Government making them aware of your request.</p>
                        <p>From what I hear, and this I have from quite trustworthy authority, the
                            motive of their coming, for the briefest stay in the United States, was
                            a desire to see their relatives in this season, and they had no
                            other.</p>
                        <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_JJAAJ1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Jusserand</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>